definition: the system of those sequential relations that any event has to any other, as past, present, or future; indefinite and continuous duration regarded as that in which events succeed one another.

a period of 365 or 366 days, in the gregorian calendar, divided into 12 calendar months, now reckoned as beginning jan. 1 and ending dec. 31 (calendar year,  or civil year ).compare common year, leap year.
persons indefinitely or collectively; persons in general: to find it easy to talk to people; what will people think?
manner, mode, or fashion: a new way of looking at a matter; to reply in a polite way.
an adult male person. compare woman (def. 1), boy (def. 1).
the interval of light between two successive nights; the time between sunrise and sunset: since there was no artificial illumination, all activities had to be carried on during the day.
a material object without life or consciousness; an inanimate object.
a person between birth and puberty or full growth: books for children.

the political direction and control exercised over the actions of the members, citizens, or inhabitants of communities, societies, and states; direction of the affairs of a state, community, etc.; political administration: government is necessary to the existence of civilized society.
exertion or effort directed to produce or accomplish something; labor; toil.

the condition that distinguishes organisms from inorganic objects and dead organisms, being manifested by growth through metabolism, reproduction, and the power of adaptation to environment through changes originating internally.
an adult female person.compare man (def. 1), girl (def. 1).
an assemblage or combination of things or parts forming a complex or unitary whole: a mountain system; a railroad system.
an instance of the occurrence, existence, etc., of something: sailing in such a storm was a case of poor judgment.
a portion or division of a whole that is separate or distinct; piece, fragment, fraction, or section; constituent: the rear part of the house;to glue the two parts together.
any collection or assemblage of persons or things; cluster; aggregation: a group of protesters; a remarkable group of paintings.
a numeral or group of numerals.
the earth or globe, considered as a planet.
a building in which people live; residence for human beings.
any particular extent of space or surface; part: the dark areas in the painting; the dusty area of the room.
a number of individuals assembled or associated together; group of people.
any question or matter involving doubt, uncertainty, or difficulty.
an act of helpful activity; help; aid: to do someone a service.
a particular portion of space, whether of definite or indefinite extent.
the terminal, prehensile part of the upper limb in humans and other primates, consisting of the wrist, metacarpal area, fingers, and thumb.
a social gathering, as of invited guests at a private home, for conversation, refreshments, entertainment, etc.: a cocktail party.
an institution where instruction is given, especially to persons under college age: the children are at school.
a state or nation: what european countries have you visited?
a sharp or tapering end, as of a dagger.
a period of seven successive days: that wallpapering i thought i could do in two days ended up taking me a whole week.
a person, animal, plant, group, etc., that is part of a society, party, community, taxon, or other body.
the last part or extremity, lengthwise, of anything that is longer than it is wide or broad: the end of a street;the end of a rope.
the condition of a person or thing, as with respect to circumstances or attributes: a state of health.

a unit of language, consisting of one or more spoken sounds or their written representation, that functions as a principal carrier of meaning. words are composed of one or more morphemes and are either the smallest units susceptible of independent use or consist of two or three such units combined under certain linking conditions, as with the loss of primary accent that distinguishes the one-word blackbird (primary stress on “black”, and secondary stress on “bird”) from black bird (primary stress on both words). words are usually separated by spaces in writing, and are distinguished phonologically, as by accent, in many languages.

a basic social unit consisting of parents and their children, considered as a group, whether dwelling together or not: the traditional family. a social unit consisting of one or more adults together with the children they care for: a single-parent family.
something that actually exists; reality; truth: your fears have no basis in fact.
the upper part of the body in humans, joined to the torso by the neck and containing the brain, eyes, ears, nose, and mouth.
also called calendar month.  any of the twelve parts, as january or february, into which the calendar year is divided.
one of the surfaces forming the outside of or bounding a thing, or one of the lines bounding a geometric figure.
an occupation, profession, or trade: his business is poultry farming.
the period of darkness between sunset and sunrise.

the organ of sight, in vertebrates typically one of a pair of spherical bodies contained in an orbit of the skull and in humans appearing externally as a dense, white, curved membrane, or sclera, surrounding a circular, colored portion, or iris, that is covered by a clear, curved membrane, or cornea, and in the center of which is an opening, or pupil, through which light passes to the retina.
a house, apartment, or other shelter that is the usual residence of a person, family, or household.
a sentence in an interrogative form, addressed to someone in order to get information in reply.
knowledge communicated or received concerning a particular fact or circumstance; news: information concerning a crime.
ability to do or act; capability of doing or accomplishing something.
the act or fact of changing; fact of being changed: they are pleased by the change in their son's behavior.
the feeling of a person whose attention, concern, or curiosity is particularly engaged by something: she has a great interest in the poetry of donne.
the act or process of developing;  growth; progress: child development; economic development.
any circulating medium of exchange, including coins, paper money,  and demand deposits.
a handwritten or printed work of fiction or nonfiction, usually on sheets of paper fastened or bound together within covers.

a transparent, odorless, tasteless liquid, a compound of hydrogen and oxygen, h2o, freezing at 32°f or 0°c and boiling at 212°f or 100°c, that in a more or less impure state constitutes rain, oceans, lakes, rivers, etc.: it contains 11.188 percent hydrogen and 88.812 percent oxygen, by weight.
the other one: each praises the other.
external appearance of a clearly defined area, as distinguished from color or material; configuration: a triangular form.
a portion of space within a building or other structure, separated by walls or partitions from other parts: a dining room.
a device used for determining or adjusting something to a horizontal surface.
a vehicle running on rails, as a streetcar  or railroad car.
an assembly of persons summoned or convened for consultation, deliberation, or advice.
a definite course of action adopted for the sake of expediency, facility, etc.: we have a new company policy.
an open place or a covered building where buyers and sellers convene for the sale of goods; a marketplace: a farmers' market.
law.  a place where justice is administered. a judicial tribunal duly constituted for the hearing and determination of cases. a session of a judicial assembly.
something that is produced by an agency or cause; result; consequence: exposure to the sun had the effect of toughening his skin.
something that happens as a consequence; outcome.
any conception existing in the mind as a result of mental understanding, awareness, or activity.
the act of employing, using, or putting into service: the use of tools.
application of the mind to the acquisition of knowledge, as by reading, investigation, or reflection: long hours of study.
a piece of work, especially a specific task done as part of the routine of one's occupation or for an agreed price: she gave him the job of mowing the lawn.
a word or a combination of words by which a person, place, or thing, a body or class, or any object of thought is designated, called, or known.
the physical structure and material substance of an animal or plant, living or dead.
an account or statement describing in detail an event, situation, or the like, usually as the result of observation, inquiry, etc.: a report on the peace conference; a medical report on the patient.
a mark or stroke long in proportion to its breadth, made with a pen, pencil, tool, etc., on a surface: a line down the middle of the page.

the principles and regulations established in a community by some authority and applicable to its people, whether in the form of legislation or of custom and policies recognized and enforced by judicial decision.
the front part of the head, from the forehead to the chin.
a person attached to another by feelings of affection or personal regard.
the power to determine, adjudicate, or otherwise settle issues or disputes; jurisdiction; the right to control, command, or determine.
a long, narrow stretch with a smoothed or paved surface, made for traveling by motor vehicle, carriage, etc., between two or more points; street or highway.
a person authorized to conduct religious worship; member of the clergy; pastor.
the amount of a charge or payment with reference to some basis of calculation: a high rate of interest on loans.
a movable, usually solid, barrier for opening and closing an entranceway, cupboard, cabinet, or the like, commonly turning on hinges or sliding in grooves.
a period of time equal to one twenty-fourth of a mean solar or civil day and equivalent to 60 minutes: he slept for an hour.
a room, set of rooms, or building where the business of a commercial or industrial organization or of a professional person is conducted: the main office of an insurance company; a doctor's office.
a just claim or title, whether legal, prescriptive, or moral: you have a right to say what you please.
a conflict carried on by force of arms, as between nations or between parties within a nation; warfare, as by land, sea, or air.
(often initial capital letter) one's female parent.
a human being, whether an adult or child: the table seats four persons.
a basis or cause, as for some belief, action, fact, event, etc.: the reasons for declaring war.
an instance of seeing or beholding; visual inspection.
a word or group of words designating something, especially in a particular field, as atom in physics, quietism in theology, adze in carpentry, or district leader in politics.

a rather large interval of time that is meaningful in the life of a person, in history, etc., because of its particular characteristics: a period of illness; a period of great profitability for a company; a period of social unrest in germany.
a numerical symbol, especially an arabic numeral.
an organized group of persons associated together for religious, benevolent, cultural, scientific, political, patriotic, or other purposes.
also called police force.  an organized civil force for maintaining order, preventing and detecting crime, and enforcing the laws.
a large or important town.
a requirement, necessary duty, or obligation: there is no need for you to go there.
a social group of any size whose members reside in a specific locality, share government, and often have a common cultural and historical heritage.
a cardinal number, a thousand times one thousand.

a class or group of individual objects, people, animals, etc., of the same nature or character, or classified together because they have traits in common; category: our dog is the same kind as theirs.
the sum or amount of money or its equivalent for which anything is bought, sold, or offered for sale.
the act or power of controlling; regulation;  domination or command: who's in control here?
the process or state of acting or of being active: the machine is not in action now.
the price paid to acquire, produce, accomplish, or maintain anything: the high cost of a good meal.
the act of sending out or putting forth; promulgation; distribution: the issue of food and blankets to flood victims.
a systematic series of actions directed to some end: to devise a process for homogenizing milk.
condition with reference to place; location; situation.
a direction or route taken or to be taken.
the sixtieth part (1/60) of an hour; sixty seconds.
the act or process of imparting or acquiring general knowledge, developing the powers of reasoning and judgment, and generally of preparing oneself or others intellectually for mature life.

a number of things or persons sharing a particular characteristic, or set of characteristics, that causes them to be regarded as a group, more or less precisely defined or designated; class; category: a criminal of the most vicious type.
diligent and systematic inquiry or investigation into a subject in order to discover or revise facts, theories, applications, etc.: recent research in medicine.
that which forms a basic matter of thought, discussion, investigation, etc.: a subject of conversation.
a female child, from birth to full growth.
an indefinitely short period of time; instant: i'll be with you in a moment.
the length of time during which a being or thing has existed; length of life or existence to the time spoken of or referred to: trees of unknown age; his age is 20 years.
a father-in-law, stepfather, or adoptive father.
physical power or strength possessed by a living being: he used all his force in opening the window.
an authoritative direction or instruction; command; mandate.
relative worth, merit, or importance: the value of a college education; the value of a queen in chess.
anything done, being done, or to be done; deed; performance: a heroic act.
the substance or substances of which any physical object consists or is composed: the matter of which the earth is made.
the general condition of the body or mind with reference to soundness and vigor: good health; poor health.
one of a set of objects, such as straws or pebbles, drawn or thrown from a container to decide a question or choice by chance.
the act or process of deciding;  determination, as of a question or doubt, by making a judgment: they must make a decision between these two contestants.
a public thoroughfare, usually paved, in a village, town, or city, including the sidewalk or sidewalks.
the aggregate of manufacturing or technically productive enterprises in a particular field, often named after its principal product: the automobile industry; the steel industry.
a person who is under medical care or treatment.
a number of persons or things regarded as forming a group by reason of common attributes, characteristics, qualities, or traits; kind; sort: a class of objects used in daily living.
(in a human or other conscious being) the element, part, substance, or process that reasons, thinks, feels, wills, perceives, judges, etc.: the processes of the human mind.
a building for public christian worship.
a particular mode of being of a person or thing; existing state; situation with respect to circumstances.
a substance made from wood pulp, rags, straw, or other fibrous material, usually in thin sheets, used to bear writing or printing, for wrapping things, etc.
a long pile or heap; mass: a bank of earth;a bank of clouds.
a period of 100 years.
a part that is cut off or separated.
the state or quality of being active: there was not much activity in the stock market today. he doesn't have enough physical activity in his life.
a cardinal number, ten times ten.
an article of furniture consisting of a flat, slablike top supported on one or more legs or other supports: a kitchen table;  an operating table;a pool table.
the act of dying; the end of life; the total and permanent cessation of all the vital functions of an organism.compare brain death.

a relatively permanent enclosed construction over a plot of land, having a roof and usually windows and often more than one level, used for any of a wide variety of activities, as living, entertaining, or manufacturing.

any of the faculties, as sight, hearing, smell, taste, or touch, by which humans and animals perceive stimuli originating from outside or inside the body: my sense of smell tells me that dinner is ready.
a particular kind, species, variety, class, or group, distinguished by a common character or nature: to develop a new sort of painting;nice people, of course, but not really our sort.
a group of persons, as employees, charged with carrying out the work of an establishment or executing some undertaking.
a number of persons forming one of the sides in a game or contest: a football team.
a particular instance of personally encountering or undergoing something: my encounter with the bear in the woods was a frightening experience.
a person formally engaged in learning, especially one enrolled in a school or college; pupil: a student at yale.

a body of words and the systems for their use common to a people who are of the same community or nation, the same geographical area, or the same cultural tradition: the two languages of belgium; a bantu language; the french language; the yiddish language.
a thickly populated area, usually smaller than a city and larger than a village, having fixed boundaries and certain local powers of government.
a scheme or method of acting, doing, proceeding, making, etc., developed in advance: battle plans.
a distinct part of anything arranged in divisions; a division of a complex whole or organized system.
the act or manner of managing;  handling, direction, or control.
the first part or period of the day, extending from dawn, or from midnight, to noon.
a person or group of persons elected or appointed to perform some service or function, as to investigate, report on, or act upon a particular matter.
a thing produced by labor: products of farm and factory; the product of his thought.
habitual or customary performance; operation: office practice.
that which tends to prove or disprove something; ground for belief; proof.
the solid surface of the earth; firm or dry land: to fall to the ground.
a written or printed communication addressed to a person or organization and usually transmitted by mail.
the act of coming together: a chance meeting in the park.
(in vertebrates) the terminal part of the leg, below the ankle joint, on which the body stands and moves.
a male child, from birth to full growth, especially one less than 18 years of age.
the rear part of the human body, extending from the neck to the lower end of the spine.
an amusement or pastime: children's games.
any nourishing substance that is eaten, drunk, or otherwise taken into the body to sustain life, provide energy, promote growth, etc.
the act of uniting two or more things.
a part or character played by an actor or actress.
something that happens or is regarded as happening; an occurrence, especially one of some importance.
any part of the earth's surface not covered by a body of water; the part of the earth's surface occupied by continents and islands: land was sighted from the crow's nest.
the quality, production, expression, or realm, according to aesthetic principles, of what is beautiful, appealing, or of more than ordinary significance.
the act or an instance of supporting.
the extent to which or the limits between which variation is possible: the range of steel prices; a wide range of styles.
a single step or degree in a process; a particular phase, period, position, etc., in a process, development, or series.
a person who teaches  or instructs, especially as a profession; instructor.
the act or process of buying, selling, or exchanging commodities, at either wholesale or retail, within a country or between countries: domestic trade; foreign trade.
the sound or sounds uttered through the mouth of living creatures, especially of human beings in speaking, shouting, singing, etc.
the upper limb of the human body, especially the part extending from the shoulder to the wrist.
a heavy stick, usually thicker at one end than at the other, suitable for use as a weapon; a cudgel.
an expanse of open or cleared ground, especially a piece of land suitable or used for pasture or tillage.
the branch of knowledge dealing with past events.
a father or a mother.
an oral or written description of particular events or situations; narrative: an account of the meetings; an account of the trip.
the substance or substances of which a thing is made or composed: stone is a durable material.
a state of mind in which one is troubled; worry, anxiety, or concern: he was never free from care.
manner of being situated;  location or position with reference to environment: the situation of the house allowed for a beautiful view.
a person who has control or direction of an institution, business, etc., or of a part, division, or phase of it.
something that is contemplated, devised, or planned; plan; scheme: i have several little projects around the house that i’d like to tackle in my time off.
the state of being recorded, as in writing.
one of a number of things, or a part of something, taken to show the character of the whole: this painting is an example of his early work.
the education, instruction, or discipline of a person or thing that is being trained: he's in training for the olympics.
an opening in the wall of a building, the side of a vehicle, etc., for the admission of air or light, or both, commonly fitted with a frame in which are set movable sashes containing panes of glass.
a mixture of nitrogen, oxygen, and minute amounts of other gases that surrounds the earth and forms its atmosphere.
the state or relation of being different; dissimilarity: there is a great difference between the two.
something that makes things visible or affords illumination: all colors depend on light.

an institution of learning of the highest level, having a college of liberal arts and a program of graduate studies together with several professional schools, as of theology, law, medicine, and engineering, and authorized to confer both undergraduate and graduate degrees. continental european universities usually have only graduate or professional schools.
a married woman, especially when considered in relation to her partner in marriage.
a connection, association, or involvement.
a respectful or formal term of address used to a man: no, sir.
an essential or distinctive characteristic, property, or attribute: the chemical qualities of alcohol.
a principle or regulation governing conduct, action, procedure, arrangement, etc.: the rules of chess.
a heavy or forcible blow.
a narrative, either true or fictitious, in prose or verse, designed to interest, amuse, or instruct the hearer or reader; tale.
a sum of money demanded by a government for its support or for specific facilities or services, levied upon incomes, property, sales, etc.
a person or thing that works.
(used with a plural verb) individual facts, statistics, or items of information: these data represent the results of our analyses.
a standard or example for imitation or comparison.
the material world, especially as surrounding humankind and existing independently of human activities.
a person who holds a position of rank or authority in the army, navy, air force, or any similar organization, especially one who holds a commission.
mode of building, construction, or organization; arrangement of parts, elements, or constituents: a pyramidal structure.
a piece of furniture upon which or within which a person sleeps, rests, or stays when not well.
an institution in which sick or injured people are given medical or surgical treatment.
a procedure, technique, or way of doing something, especially in accordance with a definite plan: there are three possible methods of repairing this motor.
a single thing or person.
the act, process, or result of moving.
an individual or minute part; an item or particular.
a particular month, day, and year at which some event happened or will happen: july 4, 1776 was the date of the signing of the declaration of independence.

any of various permanent upright constructions having a length much greater than the thickness and presenting a continuous surface except where pierced by doors, windows, etc.: used for shelter, protection, or privacy, or to subdivide interior space, to support floors, roofs, or the like, to retain earth, to fence in an area, etc.

a programmable electronic device designed to accept data, perform prescribed mathematical and logical operations at high speed, and display the results of these operations. mainframes, desktop and laptop computers, tablets, and smartphones are some of the different types of computers.compare analog computer, digital computer.
the sum total of two or more quantities or sums; aggregate.
the act of drawing near: the approach of a train.

machinery.  a removable drilling or boring tool for use in a brace, drill press, or the like. a removable boring head used on certain kinds of drills, as a rock drill. a device for drilling oil wells or the like, consisting of a horizontally rotating blade or an assembly of rotating toothed wheels.
something awarded, as a payment or medal.
the highest executive officer of a modern republic, as the chief executive of the united states: sworn in as the 56th president of mexico.
a plan, design, or program of action to be followed; project.
a main division of a book, treatise, or the like, usually bearing a number or title.
a coherent group of tested general propositions, commonly regarded as correct, that can be used as principles of explanation and prediction for a class of phenomena: einstein's theory of relativity.
that which a person owns; the possession or possessions of a particular owner: they lost all their property in the fire.
a male child or person in relation to his parents.
a person or thing that directs.
a person or thing that leads.
a cardinal point of the compass lying directly opposite north. abbreviation: s
the act of putting to a special use or purpose: the application of common sense to a problem.
a partnership or association for carrying on a business.
a piece of wood sawed thin, and of considerable length and breadth compared with the thickness.
a male sovereign or monarch; a man who holds by life tenure, and usually by hereditary right, the chief authority over a country and people.
the act of producing;  creation; manufacture.

a person, usually an official, who is in charge of the records, correspondence, minutes of meetings, and related affairs of an organization, company, association, etc.: the secretary of the linguistic society of america.
the absence of any cause of events that can be predicted, understood, or controlled: often personified or treated as a positive agency: chance governs all.
an act or instance, process, or manner of functioning or operating.
an appropriate or favorable time or occasion: their meeting afforded an opportunity to exchange views.
the full or proper portion or part allotted or belonging to or contributed or owed by an individual or group.
the act of agreeing or of coming to a mutual arrangement.
a person who has authority, control, or power over others; a master, chief, or ruler.
an agreement between two or more parties for the doing or not doing of something specified.
a visual representation of a person, object, or scene, as a painting, drawing, photograph, etc.: i carry a picture of my grandchild in my wallet.
the means by which the presence, quality, or genuineness of anything is determined; a means of trial.
freedom from danger, risk, etc.; safety.
a cardinal number, 10 times 100.
the selection of a person or persons for office by vote: in 2018, elections for governors were held in 36 states.
any thing or place from which something comes, arises, or is obtained; origin: which foods are sources of calcium?
time that is to be or come hereafter.
the position or location of a town, building, etc., especially as to its environment: the site of our summer cabin.
detriment, disadvantage, or deprivation from failure to keep, have, or get: to bear the loss of a robbery.
a retail store, especially a small one.

any member of the kingdom animalia, comprising multicellular organisms that have a well-defined shape and usually limited growth, can move voluntarily, actively acquire food and digest it internally, and have sensory and nervous systems that allow them to respond rapidly to stimuli: some classification schemes also include protozoa and certain other single-celled eukaryotes that have motility and animallike nutritional modes.
the latter part of the day and early part of the night.
something that is advantageous or good; an advantage: he explained the benefits of public ownership of the postal system.

anatomy. a hollow, pumplike organ of blood circulation, composed mainly of rhythmically contractile smooth muscle, located in the chest between the lungs and slightly to the left and consisting of four chambers: a right atrium that receives blood returning from the body via the superior and inferior vena cavae, a right ventricle that pumps the blood through the pulmonary artery to the lungs for oxygenation, a left atrium that receives the oxygenated blood via the pulmonary veins and passes it through the mitral valve, and a left ventricle that pumps the oxygenated blood, via the aorta, throughout the body.
the sixteenth letter of the english alphabet, a consonant.
the reason for which something exists or is done, made, used, etc.
something considered by an authority or by general consent as a basis of comparison; an approved model.
one side of a leaf of something printed or written, as a book, manuscript, or letter.
a person licensed to practice medicine, as a physician, surgeon, dentist, or veterinarian.
one of the elements contributing to a particular result or situation: poverty is only one of the factors in crime.
any of the numerous fine, usually cylindrical, keratinous filaments growing from the skin of humans and animals; a pilus.
a profoundly tender, passionate affection for another person.
an art of sound in time that expresses ideas and emotions in significant forms through the elements of rhythm, melody, harmony, and color.
expense or cost: improvements made at a tenant's own charge.
a decorative design, as for wallpaper, china, or textile fabrics, etc.
an outline, sketch, or plan, as of the form and structure of a work of art, an edifice, or a machine to be executed or constructed.
a separate or limited portion or quantity of something: a piece of land;a piece of chocolate.
the total number of people inhabiting a country, city, or any district or area.
a plant having a permanently woody main stem or trunk, ordinarily growing to a considerable height, and usually developing branches at some distance from the ground.
acquaintance with facts, truths, or principles, as from study or investigation; general erudition: knowledge of many things.
a musical, dramatic, or other entertainment presented before an audience.

botany. any member of the kingdom plantae, comprising multicellular organisms that typically produce their own food from inorganic matter by the process of photosynthesis and that have more or less rigid cell walls containing cellulose, including vascular plants, mosses, liverworts, and hornworts: some classification schemes may include fungi, algae, bacteria, and certain single-celled eukaryotes that have plantlike qualities, as rigid cell walls or the use of photosynthesis.
the exertion of force upon a surface by an object, fluid, etc., in contact with it: the pressure of earth against a wall.
a state, process, or instance of combustion in which fuel or other material is ignited and combined with oxygen, giving off light, heat, and flame.
the aggregate of surrounding things, conditions, or influences; surroundings; milieu milieu.
a plot of ground, usually near a house, where flowers, shrubs, vegetables, fruits, or herbs are cultivated.
the spatial dimensions, proportions, magnitude, or bulk of anything: the size of a farm; the size of the fish you caught.
the separating of any material or abstract entity into its constituent elements (opposed to synthesis).
the refreshing quiet or repose of sleep: a good night's rest.
the favorable or prosperous termination of attempts or endeavors; the accomplishment of one's goals.
the product of mental activity; that which one thinks: a body of thought.
an extensive, continuous part of a surface, space, or body: a region of the earth.
the act or faculty of attending, especially by directing the mind to an object.
a series of names or other items written or printed together in a meaningful grouping or sequence so as to constitute a record: a list of members.
an existing connection; a significant association between or among things: the relation between cause and effect.
the act or state of setting or the state of being set.
the unlimited or incalculably great three-dimensional realm or expanse in which all material objects are located and all events occur.
a communication or declaration in speech or writing, setting forth facts, particulars, etc.
an urgent or pressing requirement: demands upon one's time.
an accepted or professed rule of action or conduct: a person of good moral principles.
the salt waters that cover the greater part of the earth's surface.

a movement made by lifting the foot and setting it down again in a new position, accompanied by a shifting of the weight of the body in the direction of the new position, as in walking, running, or dancing.
the city or town that is the official seat of government in a country, state, etc.: tokyo is the capital of japan.
an act or instance of choosing;  selection: her choice of a computer was made after months of research. his parents were not happy with his choice of friends.
two of the same sort considered together; pair.
a commercial establishment offering lodging to travelers and sometimes to permanent residents, and often having restaurants, meeting rooms, stores, etc., that are available to the general public.
a person or thing that plays.
a place or position in which a person or thing is normally located.
a small community or group of houses in a rural area, larger than a hamlet and usually smaller than a town, and sometimes (as in parts of the u.s.) incorporated as a municipality.
a thin layer or coating: a film of grease on a plate.
an organization of people with a common purpose and having a formal structure.
an effort made to accomplish something: he made an attempt to swim across the lake.
a prominent or conspicuous part or characteristic: tall buildings were a new feature on the skyline.
revenue received for goods or services, or from other sources, as rents or investments: for years, her only source of income was the small number of stocks her father left her.
a single human being, as distinguished from a group.
a small, open container made of china, glass, metal, etc., usually having a handle and used chiefly as a receptable from which to drink tea, soup, etc.
exertion of physical or mental power: it will take great effort to achieve victory.
the act or process of organizing.

the branch of knowledge that deals with the creation and use of technical means and their interrelation with life, society, and the environment, drawing upon such subjects as industrial arts, engineering, applied science, and pure science.
the fact or condition of being difficult.
an apparatus consisting of interrelated parts with separate functions, used in the performance of some kind of work: a sewing machine.
a small room, as in a convent or prison.
any of a series of steps or stages, as in a process or course of action; a point in any scale.
the capacity for vigorous activity; available power: i eat chocolate to get quick energy.
the act or process, or a manner of growing;  development; gradual increase.
an act or manner of treating.

full trust; belief in the powers, trustworthiness, or reliability of a person or thing: we have every confidence in their ability to succeed.
the entire body of individuals born and living at about the same time: the postwar generation.

the act, system, or business of insuring  property, life, one's person, etc., against loss or harm arising in specified contingencies, as fire, accident, death, disablement, or the like, in consideration of a payment proportionate to the risk involved.
a small metal instrument specially cut to fit into a lock and move its bolt.
a picture or design executed in paints.
a portable electronic telephone device, as a cell phone, mobile phone, or smartphone.
a small part of anything or one of a number, intended to show the quality, style, or nature of the whole; specimen.
the state of being committed.
a fight, battle, or struggle, especially a prolonged struggle; strife.
any liquid that is swallowed to quench thirst, for nourishment, etc.; beverage.
a public officer authorized to hear and decide cases in a court of law; a magistrate charged with the administration of justice.
the act of making or enacting laws.
a vessel, especially a large oceangoing one propelled by sails or engines.

a declaration of an intention or determination to inflict punishment, injury, etc., in retaliation for, or conditionally upon, some action or course: his family convinced him to take the anonymous threats seriously and call the police.
a person who visits,  as for reasons of friendship, business, duty, travel, or the like.
a collection of written or printed sheets bound together and constituting a book.
the management of any office, business, or organization; direction.
a person who writes a novel, poem, essay, etc.; the composer of a literary work, as distinguished from a compiler, translator, editor, or copyist.
the ground or parts, as of a scene, situated in the rear (opposed to foreground).
a piece of furniture with shelves, drawers, etc., for holding or displaying items: a curio cabinet; a file cabinet.
a machine for converting thermal energy into mechanical energy or power to produce force and motion.
an act of entering; entrance.
the act of introducing  or the state of being introduced.
a way of doing, being done, or happening; mode of action, occurrence, etc.: i don't like the manner in which he complained.
the act or an instance of smiling; a smiling expression of the face.
the material of which anything is made: a hard, crystalline stuff.
a person who suffers from a destructive or injurious action or agency: a victim of an automobile accident.
a common unit of linear measure in english-speaking countries, equal to 3 feet or 36 inches, and equivalent to 0.9144 meter.
a large motor vehicle, having a long body, equipped with seats or benches for passengers, usually operating as part of a scheduled service; omnibus.
a beverage consisting of a decoction or infusion of the roasted ground or crushed seeds (coffee beans ) of the two-seeded fruit (coffee berry ) of certain coffee trees.
the act or process of investigating  or the condition of being investigated.
a natural elevation of the earth's surface rising more or less abruptly to a summit, and attaining an altitude greater than that of a hill, usually greater than 2,000 feet (610 meters).
a law, rule, or other order prescribed by authority, especially to regulate  conduct: safety regulations require the use of impact-resistant helmets.
alleviation, ease, or deliverance through the removal of pain, distress, oppression, etc.
a number of persons or things arranged in a line, especially a straight line: a row of apple trees.
a short metrical composition intended or adapted for singing,  especially one in rhymed stanzas; a lyric; a ballad.
often wages. money that is paid or received for work or services, as by the hour, day, or week.compare living wage, minimum wage.
any general or comprehensive division; a class.
a person or thing that consumes.
the main meal of the day, eaten in the evening or at midday.
an exhibiting,  showing, or presenting to view.

a game in which two opposing teams of 11 players each defend goals at opposite ends of a field having goal posts at each end, with points being scored chiefly by carrying the ball across the opponent's goal line and by place-kicking or drop-kicking the ball over the crossbar between the opponent's goal posts.compare conversion (def. 13), field goal (def. 1), safety (def. 6), touchdown.
a formal meeting in which one or more persons question, consult, or evaluate another person: a job interview.
the food served and eaten especially at one of the customary, regular occasions for taking food during the day, as breakfast, lunch, or supper.
a traveling around from place to place.

the handing down of statements, beliefs, legends, customs, information, etc., from generation to generation, especially by word of mouth or by practice: a story that has come down to us by popular tradition.
the movement of vehicles, ships, persons, etc., in an area, along a street, through an air lane, over a water route, etc.: the heavy traffic on main street.
the hard, fibrous substance composing most of the stem and branches of a tree or shrub, and lying beneath the bark; the xylem.

the act or fact of appearing,  as to the eye or mind or before the public: the unannounced appearance of dinner guests; the last appearance of caruso in aïda; her first appearance at a stockholders' meeting.
a structure spanning and providing passage over a river, chasm, road, or the like.
the act or art of constructing.
the act of contrasting; the state of being contrasted.
a statement, picture in words, or account that describes; descriptive  representation.
training to act in accordance with rules; drill: military discipline.
an act or instance of distributing.
the state or fact of existing;  being.
a shoe, especially a woman's shoe, with a flat heel or no heel.
a man  of good family, breeding, or social position.
any shelter, lodging, or dwelling place.
an act of improving  or the state of being improved.
either of the two fleshy parts or folds forming the margins of the mouth and functioning in speech.
the sitting together of a court, council, legislature, or the like, for conference or the transaction of business: congress is now in session.
a large rectangular piece of cotton, linen, or other material used as an article of bedding, commonly spread in pairs so that one is immediately above and the other immediately below the sleeper.
the group of spectators at a public event; listeners or viewers collectively, as in attendance at a theater or concert: the audience was respectful of the speaker's opinion.
a system for communication by telegraph, heliograph, etc., in which long and short sounds, light flashes, etc., are used to symbolize the content of a message: morse code.

informal interchange of thoughts, information, etc., by spoken words; oral communication between persons; talk: how to master the art of conversation. such interchange by sign language, email, or other nonoral means of communication: i enjoy our time on the phone, but she prefers conversation by texting. an instance of this: i had a long phone conversation with my cousin in florida.
a stage in a sequence of events at which the trend of all future events, especially for better or for worse, is determined; turning point.
the act of lending; a grant of the temporary use of something: the loan of a book.
a nonreigning male member of a royal family.
a person or thing that represents  another or others.
a useful and desirable thing or quality: organizational ability is an asset.
the act or process of explaining.
the act, manner, or power of flying.
the state of being free  or at liberty rather than in confinement or under physical restraint: he won his freedom after a retrial.
the final, utmost, or furthest boundary or point as to extent, amount, continuance, procedure, etc.: the limit of his experience;the limit of vision.

a publication that is issued periodically, usually bound in a paper cover, and typically contains essays, stories, poems, etc., by many writers, and often photographs and drawings, frequently specializing in a particular subject or area, as hobbies, news, or sports.

a fixed amount, other than wages, paid at regular intervals to a person or to the person's surviving dependents in consideration of past services, age, merit, poverty, injury or loss sustained, etc.: a retirement pension.
a shallow, usually circular dish, often of earthenware or porcelain, from which food is eaten.
water that is condensed from the aqueous vapor in the atmosphere and falls to earth in drops more than 0.02 inch (0.5 millimeters) in diameter.compare drizzle (def. 6).
a particular, detail, or point (usually preceded by in): to differ in some respect.
the act of a person or thing that writes.
the ability to receive or contain: this hotel has a large capacity.
a call or summons to engage in any contest, as of skill, strength, etc.
a succession of images, thoughts, or emotions passing through the mind during sleep.
a building or group of buildings with facilities for the manufacture of goods.
the management of revenues; the conduct or transaction of money matters generally, especially those affecting the public, as in the fields of banking and investment.
an act or instance of selecting or the state of being selected; choice.
a leap, jump, or bound.
a success or triumph over an enemy in battle or war.
a period or interval of time: to wait a long while;he arrived a short while ago.
the condition of being young.
any machine supported for flight in the air by buoyancy or by the dynamic action of air on its surfaces, especially powered airplanes, gliders, and helicopters.
a period of ten years: the three decades from 1776 to 1806.
the act of defining,  or of making something definite, distinct, or clear: we need a better definition of her responsibilities.

the roundish reproductive body produced by the female of certain animals, as birds and most reptiles, consisting of an ovum and its envelope of albumen, jelly, membranes, egg case,  or shell, according to species.
the act of examining;  inspection; inquiry; investigation.
an act or instance of determining mentally upon some action or result.
a visible impression or trace on something, such as a line, cut, dent, stain, or bruise: the dye left a small mark on his arm.
an announcement or intimation of something impending; warning: a day's notice.
the act of turning out; production: the factory's output of cars; artistic output.
the act of reducing  or the state of being reduced.
the faculty of conscious and especially of deliberate action; the power of control the mind has over its own actions: the freedom of the will.
a speech or written statement, usually formal, directed to a particular group of persons: the president's address on the state of the economy.
a fixed mutual agreement for a meeting; engagement: we made an appointment to meet again.
a room  furnished and used for sleeping.
the lowest or deepest part of anything, as distinguished from the top: the bottom of a hill;the bottom of a page.
the act of concentrating; the state of being concentrated.
a project undertaken or to be undertaken, especially one that is important or difficult or that requires boldness or energy: to keep the peace is a difficult enterprise.
(used as a familiar form of address.)
the point, part, position, etc., equidistant from extremes or limits.

law. the killing of another human being under conditions specifically covered in law. in the u.s., special statutory definitions include murder committed with malice aforethought, characterized by deliberation or premeditation or occurring during the commission of another serious crime, as robbery or arson (first-degree murder,  ormurder one ), and murder by intent but without deliberation or premeditation (second-degree murder,  ormurder two ).
the part of the body of an animal or human being that connects the head and the trunk.
an act, instance, or period of running: she took a five-minute run before breakfast.
a strip of cloth, paper, or plastic with an adhesive surface, used for sealing, binding, or attaching items together; adhesive tape  or masking tape.
any instrument or device for use in attack or defense in combat, fighting, or war, as a sword, rifle, or cannon.
state of being away or not being present: i acted as supervisor in his absence. your absence was noted on the records.

chemistry. a compound usually having a sour taste and capable of neutralizing alkalis and reddening blue litmus paper, containing hydrogen that can be replaced by a metal or an electropositive group to form a salt, or containing an atom that can accept a pair of electrons from a base. acids are proton donors that yield hydronium ions in water solution, or electron-pair acceptors that combine with electron-pair donors or bases.
an assembling or coming together of a number of persons, usually for a particular purpose: the principal will speak to all the students at friday's assembly.
an act or instance of being born: the day of his birth.
a portable container for holding liquids, characteristically having a neck and mouth and made of glass or plastic.
the act of passing judgment as to the merits of anything.

the organ of hearing and equilibrium in vertebrates, in humans consisting of an external ear that gathers sound vibrations, a middle ear in which the vibrations resonate against the tympanic membrane, and a fluid-filled internal ear that maintains balance and that conducts the tympanic vibrations to the auditory nerve, which transmits them as impulses to the brain.
a deviation from accuracy or correctness; a mistake, as in action or speech: his speech contained several factual errors.
the act or practice of instructing  or teaching; education.
a separable component, frequently one that is interchangeable with others, for assembly into units of differing size, complexity, or function.
the act or state of settling or the state of being settled.
an establishment where merchandise is sold, usually on a retail basis.
the act or profession of a person who teaches.
a means or system of transferring.
a disturbance on the surface of a liquid body, as the sea or a lake, in the form of a moving ridge or swell.
the bed of a stream, river, or other waterway.
a constituent part; element; ingredient.
the act of cutting; a stroke or a blow, as with a knife, whip, etc.
a longing or craving, as for something that brings satisfaction or enjoyment: a desire for fame.
a charge or payment for professional services: a doctor's fee.
something granted, as a privilege or right, a sum of money, or a tract of land: several major foundations made large grants to fund the research project.
something implied  or suggested as naturally to be inferred or understood: to resent an implication of dishonesty.
a society or organization for carrying on a particular work, as of a literary, scientific, or educational character.
the first or foremost place; position in advance of others: he took the lead in the race.
a light midday meal between breakfast and dinner; luncheon.
a picture produced by photography.
the state or feeling of being pleased.
an act of recognizing or the state of being recognized.
a state in which the supreme power rests in the body of citizens entitled to vote and is exercised by representatives chosen directly or indirectly by them.
a person whose business it is to solicit  business, trade, etc.

a measure of the warmth or coldness of an object or substance with reference to some standard value. the temperature of two systems is the same when the systems are in thermal equilibrium. abbreviation: t
useless consumption or expenditure; use without adequate return; an act or instance of wasting: the project was a waste of material, money, time, and energy.
the state of the atmosphere with respect to wind, temperature, cloudiness, moisture, pressure, etc.
a solid mass of wood, stone, etc., usually with one or more flat or approximately flat faces.

anatomy, zoology. the part of the central nervous system enclosed in the cranium of humans and other vertebrates, consisting of a soft, convoluted mass of gray and white matter and serving to control and coordinate the mental and physical actions.
the act of expending  something, especially funds; disbursement; consumption.

a test, trial, or tentative procedure; an act or operation for the purpose of discovering something unknown or of testing a principle, supposition, etc.: a chemical experiment; a teaching experiment; an experiment in living.
a person who spends some time at another person's home in some social activity, as a visit, dinner, or party.
a person who guides, especially one hired to guide travelers, tourists, hunters, etc.
the people of a house collectively; a family including its servants.
a person formally educated and trained in the care of the sick or infirm.compare nurse-midwife, nurse-practitioner, physician's assistant, practical nurse, registered nurse.
a plan of action to accomplish a specified end: a school lunch program.
the act of publishing  a book, periodical, map, piece of music, engraving, or the like.
a movable or fixed device, usually consisting of a covered frame, that provides shelter, serves as a partition, etc.
absence of any sound or noise; stillness.
a formal agreement between two or more states in reference to peace, alliance, commerce, or other international relations.
something taken for granted; a supposition: a correct assumption.
a person who is at the head of or in authority over others; chief; leader.

(initial capital letter)  the national legislative body of the u.s., consisting of the senate, or upper house, and the house of representatives, or lower house, as a continuous institution. this body as it exists for a period of two years during which it has the same membership: the ninety-seventh congress. a session of this body: to speak in congress.
the act or state of connecting.
something that goes on top of or surrounds, such as the lid of a container or the binding of a book.
a large number of persons gathered closely together; throng: a crowd of angry people.
the aggregate of courses of study given in a school, college, university, etc.: the school is adding more science courses to its curriculum.
an introductory act or step; leading action: to take the initiative in making friends.
a traveling from one place to another, usually taking a rather long time; trip: a six-day journey across the desert.

a representation, usually on a flat surface, as of the features of an area of the earth or a portion of the heavens, showing them in their respective forms, sizes, and relationships according to some convention of representation: a map of canada.

any of a class of elementary substances, as gold, silver, or copper, all of which are crystalline when solid and many of which are characterized by opacity, ductility, conductivity, and a unique luster when freshly fractured.
sound, especially of a loud, harsh, or confused kind: deafening noises.
any of the major appearances or aspects in which a thing of varying modes or conditions manifests itself to the eye or mind.
a small body of standing water; pond.
an expert in science,  especially one of the physical or natural sciences.

the act of searching; careful examination or investigation: her date with the guy she met online went badly, so her search for “mr. right” continues. an instance of this: did the search turn up any clues?
the following of one thing after another; succession.
the region of the clouds or the upper air; the upper atmosphere of the earth: airplanes in the sky; cloudy skies.
the aggregate of two or more numbers, magnitudes, quantities, or particulars as determined by or as if by the mathematical process of addition: the sum of 6 and 8 is 14.
a journey or voyage: to win a trip to paris.
swift and intense force: the violence of a storm.
a small domesticated carnivore, felis domestica or f. catus, bred in a number of varieties.
an act or instance of displaying; exhibition: a display of courage.
a raised area, often having a stepped or sloping floor, in a theater, church, or other public building to accommodate spectators, exhibits, etc.
a movable barrier, usually on hinges, closing an opening in a fence, wall, or other enclosure.
a weapon consisting of a metal tube, with mechanical attachments, from which projectiles are shot by the force of an explosive; a piece of ordnance.
the state of a body perceived as having or generating a relatively high degree of warmth.
a mechanical tool or implement, especially one used for delicate or precision work: surgical instruments.
a place of settlement, activity, or residence: this town is a good location for a young doctor.
the service, functions, or profession of a minister  of religion.
a teacher of the highest academic rank in a college or university, who has been awarded the title professor in a particular branch of learning; a full professor: a professor of spanish literature.
the action or practice of a person who reads.
a subject of discourse, discussion, meditation, or composition; topic: the need for world peace was the theme of the meeting.
the act of combining or the state of being combined.
a trip in a vehicle, especially a short pleasure trip: a sunday drive in the country.
confidence or trust in a person or thing: faith in another's ability.
the place or state of punishment of the wicked after death; the abode of evil and condemned spirits; gehenna or tartarus.
the act of interpreting;  elucidation; explication: this writer's work demands interpretation.
the act or process of acquiring knowledge or skill: students exhibit a clear love of learning, enjoying the relationships they have with their teachers.
an act or instance of making or becoming open.
the state or quality of being earlier in time, occurrence, etc.
usually prospects .  an apparent probability of advancement, success, profit, etc. the outlook for the future: good business prospects.
a person who serves in an army; a person engaged in military service.
a rounded mark or stain made by foreign matter, as mud, blood, paint, ink, etc.; a blot or speck.
an implement, especially one held in the hand, as a hammer, saw, or file, for performing or facilitating mechanical operations.

(in most vertebrates) one of the hard bodies or processes usually attached in a row to each jaw, serving for the prehension and mastication of food, as weapons of attack or defense, etc., and in mammals typically composed chiefly of dentin surrounding a sensitive pulp and covered on the crown with enamel.
an assemblage of persons or things; company; band.

a choice limited to one of two or more possibilities, as of things, propositions, or courses of action, the selection of which precludes any other possibility: you have the alternative of riding or walking.
the air inhaled and exhaled in respiration.
a fortified, usually walled residence, as of a prince or noble in feudal times.
a black or dark-brown combustible mineral substance consisting of carbonized vegetable matter, used as a fuel.compare anthracite, bituminous coal, lignite.
any of various types of headgear worn by a monarch as a symbol of sovereignty, often made of precious metal and ornamented with valuable gems.
movement in or as if in a stream.
a narrow way or passage between hedges, fences, walls, or houses.
writings in which expression and form, in connection with ideas of permanent and universal interest, are characteristic or essential features, as poetry, novels, history, biography, and essays.
the state of being a member,  as of a society or club.
an error in action, calculation, opinion, or judgment caused by poor reasoning, carelessness, insufficient knowledge, etc.
the action or process of moving or of changing place or position; movement.
a freeing or releasing from confinement, obligation, pain, emotional strain, etc.
the income of a government from taxation, excise duties, customs, or other sources, appropriated to the payment of the public expenses.
the total amount; sum; aggregate: a total of $200.
the act, process, or accident of varying in condition, character, or degree: prices are subject to variation.
either of the two forelimbs of most birds and of bats, corresponding to the human arms, that are specialized for flight.
the part or edge of a surface or area that forms its outer boundary.
a standard of judgment or criticism; a rule or principle for evaluating or testing something.
an individual occurrence or event.

(in a nonfiction book, monograph, etc.) a more or less detailed alphabetical listing of names, places, and topics along with the numbers of the pages on which they are mentioned or discussed, usually included in or constituting the back matter.
a portion or section of a written work; a paragraph, verse, etc.: a passage of scripture.
a shaped piece of fabric attached inside or outside a garment and forming a pouch used especially for carrying small articles.

a typically circular band of metal or other durable material, especially one of gold or other precious metal, often set with gems, for wearing on the finger as an ornament, a token of betrothal or marriage, etc.
the state of being suggested.
an elongated depression between uplands, hills, or mountains, especially one following the course of a stream.

a person or thing that wins; victor: all three winners received plaques for their winning presentations.a yearling teeswater sheep took the limelight yesterday when it was crowned the overall winner of the interbreed wool on the hoof competition.
a cardinal number represented in the u.s. by 1 followed by 9 zeros, and in great britain by 1 followed by 12 zeros.
a distinguishing feature or quality: generosity is his chief characteristic.
a person appointed or authorized to act as a substitute for another or others.
a thing made for a particular purpose; an invention or contrivance, especially a mechanical or electrical one.

the art or science of making practical application of the knowledge of pure sciences, as physics or chemistry, as in the construction of engines,  bridges, buildings, mines, ships, and chemical plants.
the basis or groundwork of anything: the moral foundation of both society and religion.
any product of plant growth useful to humans or animals.
a body of fresh or salt water of considerable size, surrounded by land.
one of the expanded, usually green organs borne by the stem of a plant.

a set of beliefs concerning the cause, nature, and purpose of the universe, especially when considered as the creation of a superhuman agency or agencies, usually involving devotional and ritual observances, and often containing a moral code  governing the conduct of human affairs.
the state of being represented.
the act of asking for something to be given or done, especially as a favor or courtesy; solicitation or petition: at his request, they left.
an establishment where meals are served to customers.
a person who devotes himself or herself to one subject or to one particular branch of a subject or pursuit.
a rectangle having all four sides of equal length.
an act or instance of surprising or being surprised.
any sound considered with reference to its quality, pitch, strength, source, etc.: shrill tones.
an act or instance of walking, or going on foot at a moderate pace.

a series of objects connected one after the other, usually in the form of a series of metal rings passing through one another, used either for various purposes requiring a flexible tie with high tensile strength, as for hauling, supporting, or confining, or in various ornamental and decorative forms.
a closed plane curve consisting of all points at a given distance from a point within it called the center. equation: x2 + y2 = r2.
the act of producing or causing to exist; the act of creating;  engendering.
an act or instance of falling or dropping from a higher to a lower place or position.
an act or instance of noticing or perceiving.
the present time: she has one foot in the present and one foot in the future.
a discharge of a firearm, bow, etc.
an act or instance of striking.
the gaseous envelope surrounding the earth; the air: a weather balloon rising high into the atmosphere.
the distinction or condition of being a champion: to win a championship.
grammar. a syntactic construction containing a subject and predicate and forming part of a sentence or constituting a whole simple sentence.
the land next to the sea; seashore: the rocky coast of maine.
law. a person, company, etc., against whom a claim or charge is brought in a court (opposed to plaintiff).
an article of furniture having a broad, usually level, writing surface, as well as drawers or compartments for papers, writing materials, etc.
a marking off or distinguishing  as different: his distinction of sounds is excellent.
a person who feels hatred for, fosters harmful designs against, or engages in antagonistic activities against another; an adversary or opponent.
a prevailing custom or style of dress, etiquette, socializing, etc.: the latest fashion in dresses.
one of several deities, especially a male deity, presiding over some portion of worldly affairs.compare goddess (def. 1).
a strong effect produced on the intellect, feelings, conscience, etc.
the position or function of a leader,  a person who guides or directs a group: he managed to maintain his leadership of the party despite heavy opposition.
the act of buying or selling in a market.
a body of coherent matter, usually of indefinite shape and often of considerable size: a mass of dough.
an assembly of moving parts performing a complete functional motion, often being part of a large machine; linkage.

a distinct portion, section, or division of a wall, wainscot, ceiling, door, shutter, fence, etc., especially of any surface sunk below or raised above the general level or enclosed by a frame or border.
an overthrow or repudiation and the thorough replacement of an established government or political system by the people governed.

a drop of the saline, watery fluid continually secreted by the lacrimal glands between the surface of the eye and the eyelid, serving to moisten and lubricate these parts and keep them clear of foreign particles.
a forward movement; progress in space: the advance of the troops to the border.
an expanse of sand or pebbles along a shore.
the act of a person or thing that draws.
an outer garment for women and girls, consisting of bodice and skirt in one piece.
a person trained and skilled in the design, construction, and use of engines  or machines, or in any of various branches of engineering: a mechanical engineer; a civil engineer.
the act or an instance of establishing.
any device for producing a current of air by the movement of a broad surface or a number of such surfaces.

chemistry. a ductile, malleable, silver-white metallic element, scarcely known in a pure condition, but much used in its crude or impure carbon-containing forms for making tools, implements, machinery, etc. symbol: fe; atomic weight: 55.847; atomic number: 26; specific gravity: 7.86 at 20°c.compare cast iron, pig iron, steel, wrought iron.
liabilities, finance. moneys owed; debts or pecuniary obligations (opposed to assets).accounting. liabilities as detailed on a balance sheet, especially in relation to assets and capital.
an opaque white or bluish-white liquid secreted by the mammary glands of female mammals, serving for the nourishment of their young.
a comparatively small and powerful engine, especially an internal-combustion engine in an automobile, motorboat,  or the like.
mutual discussion and arrangement of the terms of a transaction or agreement: the negotiation of a treaty.

the part of the face or facial region in humans and certain animals that contains the nostrils and the organs of smell and functions as the usual passageway for air in respiration: in humans it is a prominence in the center of the face formed of bone and cartilage, serving also to modify or modulate the voice.
something from which anything arises or is derived; source; fountainhead: to follow a stream to its origin.
possibility; potentiality: an investment that has little growth potential.
the external upper covering of a house or other building.
a person employed by another, especially to perform domestic duties.
an external covering for the human foot, usually of leather and consisting of a more or less stiff or heavy sole and a lighter upper part ending a short distance above, at, or below the ankle.
the portion of the earth's surface consisting of disintegrated rock and humus.
a large receptacle, container, or structure for holding a liquid or gas: tanks for storing oil.
a slip, usually of paper or cardboard, serving as evidence that the holder has paid a fare or admission or is entitled to some service, right, or the like: a railroad ticket; a theater ticket.
the good fortune, health, happiness, prosperity, etc., of a person, group, or organization; well-being: to look after a child's welfare; the physical or moral welfare of society.

anatomy, zoology.  one of the structures composing the skeleton of a vertebrate. the hard connective tissue forming the substance of the skeleton of most vertebrates, composed of a collagen-rich organic matrix impregnated with calcium, phosphate, and other minerals.

pathology.  a malignant and invasive growth or tumor, especially one originating in epithelium, tending to recur after excision and to metastasize to other sites. any disease characterized by such growths.
a person who has defeated all opponents in a competition or series of competitions, so as to hold first place: the heavyweight boxing champion.
the head or leader of an organized body of people; the person highest in authority: the chief of police.
a native or naturalized member of a state or nation who owes allegiance to its government and is entitled to its protection (distinguished from alien).

a large formal meeting or assembly, as of members, representatives, or delegates, for discussion of and action on particular matters of common concern: in 1932 he was elected president of the missouri state medical association at its annual convention.

a person having managerial and sometimes policy-making responsibility related to the writing, compilation, and revision of content for a publishing firm or for a newspaper, magazine, or other publication: she was offered a managing editor position at a small press.
cost or charge: the expense of a good meal.
combustible matter used to maintain fire, as coal, wood, oil, or gas, in order to create heat or power.

military. u.s. army and  air force. an officer ranking above a lieutenant general  and below a general of the army  or general of the air force. u.s. army. an officer of any of the five highest ranks: a brigadier general, major general, lieutenant general,  general, or general of the army. u.s. marine corps. an officer holding the highest rank in the corps. (in numerous armies) an officer in the highest, second, or third highest rank, as one ranking immediately below a field marshal in the british army.
something given  voluntarily without payment in return, as to show favor toward someone, honor an occasion, or make a gesture of assistance; present.
extent or distance upward: the balloon stopped rising at a height of 500 feet.
the official residence of a king, queen, bishop, or other sovereign or exalted personage.
a person who is confined in prison  or kept in custody, especially as the result of legal process.

that with which anything is tied.

also called ethyl alcohol, grain alcohol, ethanol,  fermentation alcohol. a colorless, limpid, volatile, flammable, water-miscible liquid, c2h5oh, having an etherlike odor and pungent, burning taste, the intoxicating principle of fermented liquors, produced by yeast fermentation of certain carbohydrates, as grains, molasses, starch, or sugar, or obtained synthetically by hydration of ethylene or as a by-product of certain hydrocarbon syntheses: used chiefly as a solvent in the extraction of specific substances, in beverages, medicines, organic synthesis, lotions, tonics, colognes, rubbing compounds, as an automobile radiator antifreeze, and as a rocket fuel.compare denatured alcohol, methyl alcohol.
anything built or serving to bar passage, as a railing, fence, or the like: people may pass through the barrier only when their train is announced.

the composite or generally prevailing weather conditions of a region, as temperature, air pressure, humidity, precipitation, sunshine, cloudiness, and winds, throughout the year, averaged over a series of years.

the cultivated produce of the ground, while growing or when gathered: the wheat crop.
the absence of light; darkness: i can't see well in the dark.
position in life as determined by wealth: it's not easy to make one's fortune from humble beginnings.
the abode of god, the angels, and the spirits of the righteous after death; the place or state of existence of the blessed after the mortal life.
an act of holding fast by a grasp of the hand or by some other physical means; grasp; grip: take hold.do you have a hold on the rope?
anything serving to indicate  or point out, as a sign or token.
extent, size, etc., ascertained by measuring.
a form of the possessive case of i used as a predicate adjective: the yellow sweater is mine.

something used for or regarded as representing something else; a material object representing something, often something immaterial; emblem, token, or sign.
a slender or pointed end or extremity, especially of anything long or tapered: the tips of the fingers.

the profession of designing buildings, open areas, communities, and other artificial constructions and environments, usually with some regard to aesthetic effect. architecture often includes design or selection of furnishings and decorations, supervision of construction work, and the examination, restoration, or remodeling of existing buildings.
a rather deep, round dish or basin, used chiefly for holding liquids, food, etc.
that which is carried; load: a horse's burden of rider and pack.
the curd of milk separated from the whey and prepared in many ways as a food.
the state of being confused.
a person who believes in the political or social equality of all people.

mathematics.  a property of space; extension in a given direction: a straight line has one dimension, a parallelogram has two dimensions, and a parallelepiped has three dimensions. the generalization of this property to spaces with curvilinear extension, as the surface of a sphere. the generalization of this property to vector spaces  and to hilbert space.  the generalization of this property to fractals, which can have dimensions that are noninteger real numbers.  extension in time: space-time has three dimensions of space and one of time.
an open, relatively shallow container of pottery, glass, metal, wood, etc., used for various purposes, especially for holding or serving food.
absorbing or controlling possession of the mind by any interest or pursuit; lively interest: he shows marked enthusiasm for his studies.
an act or instance of evaluating  or appraising.
an expert in history; authority on history.
the act of implementing,  or putting into effect; fulfillment: the implementation of policies to conserve energy will involve personal sacrifice.

a person who belongs to one of the professions, especially one of the learned professions.
a person or company whose business is the publishing  of books, periodicals, engravings, computer software, etc.
an act of satisfying; fulfillment; gratification.

a plan of procedure, usually written, for a proposed objective, especially with reference to the sequence of and time allotted for each item or operation necessary to its completion: the schedule allows three weeks for this stage.
any of numerous ruminant mammals of the genus ovis, of the family bovidae, closely related to the goats, especially o. aries, bred in a number of domesticated varieties.
a hard outer covering of an animal, as the hard case of a mollusk, or either half of the case of a bivalve mollusk.
the act of storing;  state or fact of being stored: all my furniture is in storage.
a comprehensive and usually brief abstract, recapitulation, or compendium of previously stated facts or statements.
a special natural ability or aptitude: a talent for drawing.
a hollow, usually cylindrical body of metal, glass, rubber, or other material, used especially for conveying or containing liquids or gases.
an act or instance of wishing.

the act of allowing to enter; entrance granted by permission, by provision or existence of pecuniary means, or by the removal of obstacles: the admission of foreign aid workers into the zone of active conflict.
anatomy, zoology. (in bipeds) the outer, front part of the thorax, or the front part of the body from the neck to the abdomen; chest.
the state or period of being a child.
personal behavior; way of acting; bearing or deportment.
the act of consulting;  conference.
a person who devises or executes designs,  especially one who creates forms, structures, and patterns, as for works of art or machines.
